ted rest mass energy into kinetic power,\nranges between 3 and 5 \\times 10^{-3}. Such a ``kinetic efficiency'' varies\nhowever strongly with SMBH mass and redshift, being maximal for very massive\nholes at late times, as required for the AGN feedback by many galaxy formation\nmodels in Cosmological contexts. (Abriged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 May 2008 10:46:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
