 coefficient analogous to Hall\nconductivity, for paired states, Laughlin states, and more general quantum Hall\nstates. Hall viscosity is an invariant within a topological phase, and is\ngenerally proportional to the \"conformal spin density\" in the ground state.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 May 2008 11:56:16 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 19 Jul 2008 16:56:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 31 Oct 2008 15:20:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-09-08"}
