pected to increase the halo concentration, the fact that we see no\nevidence of high concentrations on scales above 20% of the virial radius\nsuggests that baryonic effects are limited to small scales, and are not a\nsignificant source of uncertainty for the current weak lensing measurements of\nthe dark matter power spectrum. [ABRIDGED]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 May 2008 14:47:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 7 Jul 2008 15:32:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-18"}
